cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on analyzing meta-data of tweets to characterize political fake news on Twitter. This involves studying user behavior, account characteristics, and polarization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also touches upon social and political aspects, which could place it in cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). Additionally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the content of tweets, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the verification of users, which could place it in cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
